latestIgtvVideos.title: Your daily Skincare Routine✨❤️....
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys! Finally dropped my first 𝙄𝙜𝙩𝙫 about My Skincare Routine With natural products you'd find at your home .
.
 So this is what I usually do for my skin. But don’t be fooled because even I have been through my own struggles and it’s been a long journey now that I am confident enough to post this video for you guys. If you liked it and enjoyed watching it please like, comment and share this video as it would mean a lot to me.

𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘧𝘰𝘭𝘭𝘰𝘸𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘥𝘶𝘤𝘵𝘴 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘶𝘴𝘦𝘥 𝘪𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘷𝘪𝘥𝘦𝘰- ....
1. Coffee, potato juice , biotique bio cucumber toner, biotique -coconut skin brightening face cream , khadi aloevera gel, vaseline petroleum jelly (lipbalm)and cotton.
𝗦𝘁𝗲𝗽𝘀
- Add lil rose water or normal water to coffee and scrub your face gently and massage it upwards for 5 mins .
- Soak the cottons in potato juice and keep it on your eyes covering your under eyes to reduce puffiness and dark circles , leave it for 20 mins .
- Wash your face with any hydrating face wash that suits your skin (Remember to dab the towel not rub it) @neutrogena
-Use biotique cucumber toner @biotique_world
- apply the khadi aloevera gel.
- use the face cream (biotique) optional @biotique_world
- Apply the lip balm .@vaselineindia .

Also to say that this mask helps exfoliate your skin. (Not to use daily especially in summers cause it might affect your skin in opp ways depending
on your skin type ) 
You can use this mask once in a week.Really good for oily skin. 
For dry skin best is Honey mask (natural honey ) or Gram flour ( channe ka aata)
both helps to detan and leave your skin smooth reducing your acne marks or scars . (My everyday skincare )
Tomatoes, potatoes, Milk , cucumbers or rose water really works great for under eyes .
Any masks you use should be kept for 20 mins and rinse it off. .

I also want to take a minute to say that you are all beautiful just the way you are. Everything will get better soon and your skin will heal. 
Love yourself! ♥️
#skincare #routine #quarantine #stayhome #staysafe

latestPosts.caption:
The Sabarmati Report : My first time on silver screen ♥️

I still pinch myself, wondering if this is real. Growing up in the city of dreams, I was mesmerized by the silver screen, never imagining I’d be a part of it one day. Life had other plans, and here I am, overwhelmed with gratitude.🥺♥️
Thanks to Paapa’s blessings and Krishna’s guidance. This journey has taught me to believe in myself, work hard, and stay grateful. 🧿♥️
I wish if dad was here he’d have been the happiest to see me up on the screen 🥹🫶
To everyone who has supported me along the way, My mom and bhai , my friends,my love , my co-actors, thank you for believing in me. This is just the beginning, and I’m honored to have you all on this journey with me.♥️🥺

To all aspiring dreamers, never give up! Your dreams are within reach ♥️

Jai Shree Ram 🚩

Thankyou @castingchhabra @balajimotionpictures @vikirfilms @amulvmohan for casting me for this role and believing in me 🫶 
My co-actors @viram.bhandari @kalpana.gagdekar.chhara wouldn’t have been possible without you both ♥️

 @ektarkapoor @amulvmohan @anshulmohan @sarnadheeraj @vikrantmassey @raashiikhanna @iridhidogra  @barkhasingh0308 @aowlkan poojapraheja @k_insta_official_ @sachdevaakhilnasha @rajatdesigns @janvigill @shrey.jhawar  @zeestudiosofficial @zeecinema @zeemusiccompany @zee5 @pvrcinemas_official #jaishreeram

I’m thrilled to have made my debut in the film industry with ‘Fateh’ a project that marked Sonu Sood’s first directorial venture. 
It was an absolute privilege to share the screen with him and be a part of this milestone moment. Catch me in action as a Zee News anchor playing a cameo in ‘Fateh’! 
I’m deeply grateful to @vedishnaidu and @sonu_sood sir for trusting me with this opportunity and feel blessed to have taken the first step in my journey. 
I’m excited to see what the future holds ♥️🫶🧿🤞

#Fateh #DebutFilm #Grateful #Blessed #NewBeginnings
